        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer910415837" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3907241793746691955">Although he&apos;s liberalism&apos;s pet philosopher, the important concepts in this book are completely misguided: <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://nooilforpacifists.blogspot.com/2007/10/ask-neo-con-part-5.html'>http://nooilforpacifists.blogspot.com...</a> Not understanding economics, he basises justice on a &quot;fairness&quot; (the famous &quot;veil of ignorance&quot;) dis-coupled from economic reality and markets. It fails to account for progress, productivity, and the possibility of change. In the end, Rawls was neither a philosopher, nor a moralist--he was a liberal scold, who (regrettably) lives on providing aid and </span>
  <span id="freeText3907241793746691955" style="display:none">Although he's liberalism's pet philosopher, the important concepts in this book are completely misguided: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://nooilforpacifists.blogspot.com/2007/10/ask-neo-con-part-5.html">http://nooilforpacifists.blogspot.com...</a> Not understanding economics, he basises justice on a "fairness" (the famous "veil of ignorance") dis-coupled from economic reality and markets. It fails to account for progress, productivity, and the possibility of change. In the end, Rawls was neither a philosopher, nor a moralist--he was a liberal scold, who (regrettably) lives on providing aid and comfort to extreme movements such as "Occupy Wall Street" and environmental "back-to-the-Stone Age" doomsayers.</span>
