  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_580634576" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/580634576" />
    <a title="Sue" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9199204-sue"><img alt="Sue" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1601680776p2/9199204.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/580634576?book_show_action=true">Apr 04, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sue" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sue" href="/user/show/9199204-sue">Sue</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/435969.A_Theory_of_Justice">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9199204-sue?shelf=philosophy">philosophy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9199204-sue?shelf=politics">politics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer580634576" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9762635146727590654">Have only skimmed it - need help in understanding it so have bought Rawls by Freeman who is apparently an expert. My OU Masters Course is helping me to understand it more thoroughly - it does present difficulties for the current conservative libertarian approach. About to start his later works where he apparently clarifies many of his ideas. As a starting point for a fully systematic approach to creating a more complete normative theory of political society it cannot be beaten. I suggest it is r</span>
  <span id="freeText9762635146727590654" style="display:none">Have only skimmed it - need help in understanding it so have bought Rawls by Freeman who is apparently an expert. My OU Masters Course is helping me to understand it more thoroughly - it does present difficulties for the current conservative libertarian approach. About to start his later works where he apparently clarifies many of his ideas. As a starting point for a fully systematic approach to creating a more complete normative theory of political society it cannot be beaten. I suggest it is read alongside Anarchy, State and Utopia by Nozick and if you are a Marxist at heart make sure you read Jerry Cohen's critiques of both Rawls and Nozick. Thank you Mr Rawls for bringing political philosophy back into fashion.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9762635146727590654" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
